erryville, a small community in northwest Virginia's \"horse country\"", "url": "https://www.loc.gov/item/2020724159/"}], "resource": {"fulltext_file": "https://tile.loc.gov/text-services/word-coordinates-service?segment=/service/ndnp/vi/batch_vi_moser_ver01/data/sn85025371/00542867395/1945122701/0862.xml&format=alto_xml&full_text=1", "image": "https://tile.loc.gov/image-services/iiif/service:ndnp:vi:batch_vi_moser_ver01:data:sn85025371:00542867395:1945122701:0855/full/pct:6.25/0/default.jpg", "pdf": "https://tile.loc.gov/storage-services/service/ndnp/vi/batch_vi_moser_ver01/data/sn85025371/00542867395/1945122701/0862.pdf", "segment_count": 16, "url": "https://www.loc.gov/resource/sn85025371/1945-12-27/ed-1/", "word_coordinates": "https://tile.loc.gov/text-services/word-coordinates-service"}, "resources": [{"fulltext_file": "https://tile.loc.gov/text-services/word-coordinates-service?segment=/service/ndnp/vi/batch_vi_moser_ver01/data/sn85025371/00542867395/1945122701/0862.xml&format=alto_xml&full_text=1", "image": "https://tile.loc.gov/image-services/iiif/service:ndnp:vi:batch_vi_moser_ver01:data:sn85025371:00542867395:1945122701:0855/full/pct:6.25/0/default.jpg", "pdf": "https://tile.loc.gov/storage-services/service/ndnp/vi/batch_vi_moser_ver01/data/sn85025371/00542867395/1945122701/0862.pdf", "segment_count": 16, "url": "https://www.loc.gov/resource/sn85025371/1945-12-27/ed-1/", "word_coordinates": "https://tile.loc.gov/text-services/word-coordinates-service"}], "segment_id": "/service/ndnp/vi/batch_vi_moser_ver01/data/sn85025371/00542867395/1945122701/0862.xml", "segments": [{"access_restricted": false, "aka": ["http://www.loc.gov/resource/sn85025371/1945-12-27/ed-1/?sp=8"], "batch": ["vi_moser_ver01"], "campaigns": [], "composite_location": ["0/united states/", "1/united states/virginia/", "2/united states/virginia/clarke/", "3/united states/virginia/clarke/berryville/"], "contributor": ["library of virginia; richmond, va"], "date": "1945-12-27", "dates": ["1945-12-27"], "description": ["THE CLARKE COURIER ESTABLISHED 1800 Publisher Stacy B Lloyd Jr Managing Editor G Kenneth Levi Entered As Second Class Mail Matter at the Postoffice In Berryville Virginia Published Weekly At Berryville Clarke County Virginia Subscription Price Paid in Advance 200 a Year Six Months 125 Three Months 100 Classified Advertising Rates two cents a word Minimum charge 25 cents Display advertising rates upon request Established first by Captain Wm N Nelson Owned and edited by the late John O Crown and Joseph W Crown for 35 years and by Ralph N Dorsey for 11 years rawing by John Austen from Don Juan osed by permission of Dodd Meade and Co Publishers Kate Greenaway drawings published by permission of Frederick Warne Sc Co original publishers Thursday December 27 1945 ENTER 1946 Back in January just over a year ago General Eisenhower in speaking to his troops termed 1945 as the Victory Yar It was just after the Germans had attempted to break through the Allied lines at Bastogne that the General predicted that peace would come on the Western Front in 1945 He had seen and had expected one big Ger man push before the Nazis would throw down their arms"], "digitized": true, "extract_timestamp": "2024-09-29T00:03:45.874Z", "group": ["ndnp/vi", "library-of-virginia-richmond-va-awardee"], "hassegments": false, "id": "http://www.loc.gov/resource/sn85025371/1945-12-27/ed-1/?sp=8", "image_url": ["https://tile.loc.gov/image-services/iiif/service:ndnp:vi:batch_vi_moser_ver01:data:sn85025371:00542867395:1945122701:0862/full/pct:6.25/0/default.jpg#h=405&w=284", "https://tile.loc.gov/image-services/iiif/service:ndnp:vi:batch_vi_moser_ver01:data:sn85025371:00542867395:1945122701:0862/full/pct:12.5/0/default.jpg#h=811&w=569", "https://tile.loc.gov/text-services/word-coordinates-service?segment=/service/ndnp/vi/batch_vi_moser_ver01/data/sn85025371/00542867395/1945122701/0862.xml&format=alto_xml"], "index": 8, "language": ["english"], "location": ["berryville", "virgini